The Grihya-Sûtras; Rules of Vedic Domestic Ceremonies, Part. 1: 
Sânkhâyana-Grihya Sûtra; 
Âsvalâyana-Grihya Sûtra; 
Pâraskara-Grihya Sûtra; 
Khâdira-Grihya Sûtra
Here we have grouped together the two Brfihmana authors (with the fictitious doubles, the great Kaushitaki, the great Aitareya) and the two corresponding Satra authors belonging to the two chief branches of the Rig veda literature; first comes one Brahmana author (for Kahola Kaushitaki is one person) with the Sfitra author connected with him, then the second Sfitra author and the corresponding Brfihmaﬂa teacher.
